Lending Loan¶

This is the business problem from Lending-club . Dataset is available for download from Kaggle - dataset

Business Problem : Find out the Loan which has chances of getting default or Model which predict the defaulter loan in future

To solve the problem , we can divide it into below parts.

  1. Import the Libraries
  2. Load the Dataset
  3. Perform EDA on dataset
  4. Data PreProcessing
  5. Feature Engineering
  6. Applying ML algorithm with pipeline
  7. Finding the best performing Algorithm
  8. Parameter tuning for Algorithm
  9. Training the data on Algorithm
  10. Predicting the output

Lets get started and explore more dataset import the required library for analysis and Machine learning

# Display , plot and delete columns has missing value more than 50%
col_name=dt_train.columns
column_name=[]
numbers=[]
missval=dt_train.isnull().sum()/len(dt_train)*100

for i in range(0,74):
    if missval[i]>50:
        column_name.append(col_name[i])
        numbers.append(missval[i])
frame={'name of element':column_name,'missing value in %':numbers}       
df_miss=pd.DataFrame(frame)
plt.figure(figsize=(20,5))

# Skewness
col_number = dt_train.select_dtypes(include=['number']).columns.tolist()
print(col_number)
for col_transform in col_number:
    skewness = scipy.stats.skew(dt_train[col_number])
print(skewness)
if skewness.all() > 0.75:
    dt_train[col_number] = np.log1p(dt_train[col_number])

pipeEse=[]
pipeEse.append(('ScaledAdaB',Pipeline([('Scaler',StandardScaler()),('AdaB',AdaBoostClassifier())])))
pipeEse.append(('ScaledGB',Pipeline([('Scaler',StandardScaler()),('GB',GradientBoostingClassifier())])))
pipeEse.append(('ScaledRFR',Pipeline([('Scaler',StandardScaler()),('RFR',RandomForestClassifier())])))
pipeEse.append(('ScaledETR',Pipeline([('Scaler',StandardScaler()),('ETR',ExtraTreesClassifier())])))

names=[]
result=[]
for name,model in pipeEse:
    kfolds=KFold(n_splits=10,random_state=7,)
    cv_results=cross_val_score(model,X_train,Y_train,cv=kfolds,scoring='accuracy',n_jobs=-1)
    result.append(cv_results)
    names.append(name)
    print(name, cv_results.mean() ,cv_results.std())

It's time apply Machine learning Algorithm on dataset and find out which algortihm gives best accuracy score with less standard deviation

  1. Right now we don't know which algo best fit for this problem
  2. we will create pipeline , in pipeline we will preprocess data with StandardScaler and on that will apply ML algorithms
  3. As dataset is large in size , so better we will start with Ensembles ,
  4. after generating the result with Ensembles, GradientBoostingClassifier performed best out ofv all.
  5. GradientBoostingClassifier gives 99% accuracy with very less std score
  6. so we will train and predict test datset with GradientBoostingClassifier

scale=StandardScaler().fit(X_train)
tran=scale.transform(X_train)
model=GradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=7,n_estimators=100)
model.fit(tran,Y_train)

model.fit(tran,Y_train)
trnsF2=scale.transform(X_test)
decision=model.predict(trnsF2)
finalScore=accuracy_score(decision,Y_test)
finalScore1=confusion_matrix(decision,Y_test)
finalScore2=classification_report(decision,Y_test)
print(finalScore)
